Philippines Stocks: Digital Telecom, JG Summit, Universal Robina

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-08-19T04:44:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/philippines-stocks-cebu-air-digital-telecommunications.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 1.5 percent to
4,339.90. The gauge rose 0.4 percent this week.  Digital Telecommunications Philippines Inc. (DGTL PM) fell
1.3 percent to 1.52 pesos, the sharpest loss since Aug. 9.
 Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)   may drop a plan
to purchase the company if regulators don’t approve the
transaction by Aug. 26, BusinessMirror reported, citing
Philippine Long Distance Chairman Manuel Pangilinan. Pangilinan
couldn’t be reached at his office for comment.  PLDT slipped 0.6 percent to 2,332 pesos.  JG Summit Holdings
Inc. (JGS)  , which owns Digital Telecom, declined 1.6 percent
to 24.40 pesos.  Universal Robina Corp. (URC)  , the nation’s second-
biggest listed food and drinks company, sank 4 percent to 42
pesos, the lowest close since July 1, on possible downgrade in
earnings forecast after CitisecOnline.com said it’s
“reviewing” its estimates for the company. Universal Robina
President Lance Gokongwei couldn’t be reached at his office for
comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
